Indian army officer Major General D. Samanwar reported a ceasefire violation as mortars were fired into India from Pakistan.
The incident prompted talks between military operations directors of both countries.
Despite denials from Islamabad, India accused Pakistan of violating a ceasefire in Kashmir.
The upcoming bus service between the two zones signifies progress after years of conflict.
Indian Prime Minister Singh aims to promote peace with Pakistan and Kashmiri militants.
The bus service, a symbol of peace, will reunite families separated for decades.
Kashmiri leaders emphasize the need for their involvement in peace talks for a lasting resolution.
